On Monday evening, the British High Commissioner Nic Hailey hosted a cocktail to mark the inaugural launch of first police unit dedicated to the fight against child sexual exploitation and abuse. The unit which is a collaboration of National Police Service and the UK's National Crime Agency Child Exploitation and Online Protection Centre represents a powerful new weapon in the fight to protect Kenyan children.Head of Child Protection Unit Grace Ndirangu, Director of Criminal Investigations Ndegwa Muhoro, International Justice Mission Director of Investigations Umazi Malingi and British National Crime Agency Commander Kelvin Lay were among those present at the event held at the High Commissioner's residence in Muthaiga.